full recipe below! 🍌🫶🏼😊 this is a tried & true recipe that I threw together a few years back and still love making whenever we have ripe bananas. it is SO GOOD and SO EASY!

YOU NEED:
8X4 LOAF PAN
PARCHMENT PAPER
PREHEAT OVEN TO 350 F

INGREDIENTS:
1 CUP FINE ALMOND FLOUR
1/4 CUP COCONUT FLOUR
1/2 TSP BAKING POWDER
1/2 TSP CINNAMON
SEA SALT
1/2 CUP COCONUT SUGAR
2 EGG
2 TBS ALMOND BUTTER (or any nut butter)
2-3 BANANAS (1 CUP)
1 TSP VANILLA EXTRACT
CHOCOLATE CHIPS

mash the bananas in a large bowl. you can leave them chunky or thoroughly mash them up! next, add in the vanilla, coconut sugar, eggs, and almond butter. mix well! once combined, add a strainer over the bowl. put the coconut flour, almond flour, baking power, cinnamon, and salt in the strainer. you can totally skip this if you want, but it does make a difference! once the flour is sifted in (or just added), mix well! once mixed add in any amount of dairy free chocolate chips you’d like. you can also do blueberries and/or nuts! coat your pan with a piece of parchment paper, pour in the batter, add extra chocolate chips / sliced banana on top if desired, and bake at 350 for 55 minutes! Let cool before cutting. Keep stored in the fridge after 24 hours!

ENJOY!! xx

a staple for us!!! so quick, so easy, SO GOOD 👏🏼 recipe below :)

INGREDIENTS:
- 1 jar or bag or sun dried tomatoes
- 1-2 cans artichoke hearts (quartered)
- 1 pack of chicken sausage or rotisserie shredded
- 2 garlic cloves 
- olive oil (or the sun dried tomato oil) 
- 1 box of pasta (we love @jovialfoods 
- 1 bag of spinach 
- 1 can coconut milk 

1. Chop garlic, cut chicken sausage (or peel rotisserie), drain artichokes. If the sun dried tomatoes are big you can also cut them in half. Get water boiling!

2. Heat garlic on pan with a little olive oil for 2-3 minutes on medium heat. Add the sun dried tomatoes for 4-5 minutes or until fragrant.

3. Add the artichokes and chicken. Turn to low-medium and mix occasionally for 5-10 minutes. Just let it cook so the flavor mixes. You can add the spinach at this time so it starts cooking.

4. Add in the coconut milk (use a grass-feed cream if you don’t want coconut milk - it doesn’t taste coconut-y though lol). Just use the creamy part of the coconut milk at the top - not the water part at the bottom!

4. Drain and add the pasta once it’s done! Mix it well. Add more olive oil if necessary!

ENJOY! 🫶🏼🤍

Recipe below! Summer cucumber salad 🍅🥒🌿 

Ingredients:

1 carton of tomatoes diced 
1/2 red onion thinly sliced

Drizzle with a 3:1 ratio of extra virgin olive oil & red wine vinegar (or white/regular balsamic). Add salt, pepper, and a dash of garlic salt to taste!

Lemon Dijon Salmon 🍋

My mom made this recipe YEARS ago and I’ve been enjoying it ever since :) This is a super quick, easy, & nourishing dinner option to pair with a carb & veggie on the side. My go-to is an arugula salad & coconut rice 👌🏼

Ingredients:
- Wild caught salmon (this was 1.3 lbs)
- 2 cloves of garlic, minced
- 2-3 tsp dijon mustard 
- 1 Tbs olive oil 
- Small squeeze of fresh lemon juice
- Salt & pepper 

Instructions:
1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees & lay the salmon on a baking sheet. I used parchment paper under it, but make sure to be careful when broiling if you use parchment!
2. Mince the garlic and then mix the garlic, Dijon, olive oil, & lemon juice. Evenly spread on salmon & top with salt and pepper. Add a few thin slices of lemon on top. 
3. Bake at 400 for 8-10 minutes (if you like it more rare do 8 minutes). Take the lemon off and then put it back in to broil on low for 3-4 minutes! Again, feel free to broil longer if you want it more cooked.
4. Enjoy! 🍋

#easyhealthymeals #healthyrecipes #nourishing #healthydinner #easydinnerideas #salmonrecipe

Peanut Butter Cup Protein Smoothie 🥜

This has been one of my go-to smoothies for yearsss! It’s so creamy and just uses staple ingredients. The trick to making it creamy is the frozen banana! It’ll make any smoothie creamier than fresh banana would. The added collagen & coconut milk make it even better! 

This smoothie is well balanced between protein, fats, & carbs but also has skin, gut health, and hormone health benefits :) 

Blend:
- 1 frozen banana
- Few ice cubes
- 1 cup of liquid (I do half milk, half water)
- 1 serving chocolate protein (using @drinkorgain plant protein)
- 1 tsp cacao powder 
- 1-2 Tbs organic PB
- 2-3 Tbs full fat coconut milk 
Optional:
- 1 serving collagen (using @truvani )
- PB powder (not shown)

Enjoy! 🤎

Healthier Super Bowl Series Part 1: Loaded Mediterranean Hummus 🫒 

If you want to make an appetizer that is simple, quick, and still flavorful and healthy then this is IT. Can’t recommend this enough! I know @benjamintorresdpt will be requesting it often for the foreseeable future 🤍 

Arrange on a plate: 
[This can also be doubled/tripled]
- 1 container hummus
- Thinly sliced red onion (I used 1/4 onion)
- 10-15 sliced kalamata olives 
- 10-15 sliced baby tomatoes 
- Drizzle of extra virgin olive oil 
- 1-2 Tbs feta cheese cheese 
- Fresh parsley for garnish 
- Salt & pepper

Serve with:
- Any type of bread or cracker! I used warm pita bread and it was perfect 

Notes:
- You can add any other Mediterranean spice or topping! It would also be great with a little added scoop or two of tzatziki :)

Enjoy!! 😊

#healthyrecipes #easyhealthymeals #superbowlappetizers #healthymeals

Healthier Super Bowl Series Part 2: Elote Dip 🥑🌱

I think I made this every week for 8 weeks straight this past summer! It’s so fresh and flavorful & it’s so easy to make :) Perfect for a last minute appetizer to bring somewhere or a quick snack 👏🏼

Mix:
- 1 can organic corn
- 1 finely chopped red pepper
- 1/4 of a red onion chopped
- 1/2 cup chopped cilantro
- 1/4 cup cotija cheese
- Fresh lime juice from 1/2-1 lime
- 1 Tbs chili lime seasoning
- Optional: avocado (it will just get brown if it sits too long so I’d only use if you’re eating right away)

Serve with tortilla chips and/or fresh veggies! 🫑 Enjoy :) 

#easyhealthymeals #healthyrecipes #nourishing #appetizers #healthyappetizers #superbowl #healthylifestyle
weekend in wilmington :)

Healthier Super Bowl Series Part 3: Buffalo Chicken Nachos 🌶️

These might just be my new favorite nachos to make! Why make regular nachos when you can make buffalo chicken nachos 👏🏼

Ingredients:
- Organic tortilla chips 
- @primalkitchenfoods buffalo sauce 
- Shredded chicken (using rotisserie)
- Thinly sliced red onion 
- Chopped green onion 
- Any shredded cheese of choice 
- Finely chopped celery (1 stalk) 
- Organic sour cream or ranch 

Instructions:
1. Mix shredded chicken with desired amount of buffalo sauce. 
2. Layer everything on a baking sheet with your desired amount of each topping (chips, chicken, cheese, onion, sour cream/ranch, extra buffalo sauce if desired). 
3. Bake at 350 for 6-9 minutes / depends how crispy you want it! Just make sure the cheese is melted.
4. Add some celery on top :) 

NOTES:
- I mixed the sour cream with a little water to make it thinner to drizzle! 
- Blue cheese instead of shredded cheese would be SO GOOD
- Pickled onion instead of regular red onion would be yummmmyyy
